Name: UCSB

Name: Buckingham Palace
Description: Buckingham Palace is the London residence and administrative headquarters of the monarchy of the United Kingdom

Name: Staples Center
Description: Staples Center (officially stylized as STAPLES Center) is a multi-purpose arena in Downtown Los Angeles. Adjacent to the L.A. Live development, it is located next to the Los Angeles Convention Center complex along Figueroa Street. The arena opened on October 17, 1999.

Name: Eiffel Tower
Description: The Eiffel Tower is a wrought-iron lattice tower on the Champ de Mars in Paris, France. It is named after the engineer Gustave Eiffel, whose company designed and built the tower.

Name: Akihabara
Description: Akihabara  is a common name for the area around Akihabara Station in the Chiyoda ward of Tokyo, Japan. Administratively, the area called Akihabara mainly belongs to the Sotokanda and Kanda-Sakumachō districts in Chiyoda. There exists an administrative district called Akihabara in the Taitō ward further north of Akihabara Station, but it is not the place people generally refer to as Akihabara.

Name: Beijing
Description: Beijing is the capital of the People's Republic of China. It is the world's most populous capital city, with over 21 million residents, located in North China, is governed as a municipality under the direct administration of the central government with 16 urban, suburban, and rural districts.
